Here’s the difference clearly. 
1---getElementById(id)= Returns one element with that ID. There can only be one element with a given ID.
2----getElementsByClassName(class)Returns all elements that have that class as an HTMLCollection. It updates automatically if the DOM changes.
3---querySelector(selector) Returns the first element that matches any CSS selector by ID, class, tag, etc.
4----querySelectorAll(selector)  Returns all elements that match the CSS selector as a NodeList. This list does not update automatically if the DOM changes.

