Event Bubbling is when an event starts at the target element and then moves up through its parent elements all the way to the document.

How it's work---If you click a button inside a div:
when this event have been complete---Button → Div → Body → Document .

The click event first triggers on the button, then on its parent div, then body, and finally the document.

This is the default behavior for most events in JavaScript.

It allows parent elements to respond to events that happen on their children.

