Event Delegation is a technique where you attach one event listener to a parent element instead of adding listeners to each child element. The parent then checks which child triggered the event.

                                                  ---------Why it’s useful:-----

1.Better performance – fewer event listeners.

2.Works for dynamic elements – elements added later still respond.

3.Cleaner code – keeps your JavaScript simpler and easier to maintain.

